-- BP, BG, Total, Tullow Oil Will Explore for Crude in Uruguay
-- B y   P a b l o   G o n z a l e z   a n d   L u c i a   B a l d o m i r
-- 2012-10-05T19:57:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-05/bp-signs-contracts-to-explore-three-offshore-blocks-in-uruguay.html
BP Plc (BP/) ,  BG Group Plc (BG/) ,  Total SA (FP)  and
 Tullow Oil Plc (TLW)  signed production sharing contracts for eight
deep-water exploration blocks off  Uruguay ’s coast.  The companies had won the contracts in Uruguay’s second
offshore licensing round in March, the government said in a
statement today.  “In a few days the first two seismic vessels from Total
will arrive and the other companies will start to work in
2013,” said Raul Sendic, president of Uruguayan state oil
company Ancap. “Companies will invest around $1.5 billion.”  To contact the reporters on this story:
